title: Southeast Regional Series: Event #1 Begin, Believe
Junior Regional Championship
description: This event is the USA Cycling Southeast Regional Championship for Juniors.  All junior riders age 9-18 will be eligible to compete for the championship, and in their unique age groups just like the National Championships.
course: The West Oak Crit course has been used for races, and is a common training spot for riders in the Atlanta area.  The course is a safe, and wide open course, with no real technical sections.  It is an ideal course for a beginner, or an experienced junior.
registration: Riders can pre-register at USA Cycling, or register on-site.  All riders are required to have either a USA Cycling annual, or one-day license.  The one-day license is $15, and an annual license is $35.  All riders, and a parent/guardian, will be required to sign the waiver for this event.
notes: This wheel pit will be a wheel in/wheel out pit, so bring any spare wheels you have in case of a mishap.  Junior gearing is required, so please make sure you have your gearing checked by a local bike shop.  The gear restriction is 7.93 meters (26 feet) and is the equivalent of a 52 x 14 maximum gear.  Juniors will be required to go through roll-out, and riders who do not pass will be relegated.
directions: The race address is 1975 West Oak Circle, Marietta, GA 30062.

title: Wrenched Bicycles Oakwood City Park Classic
Georgia State Road Race Championship Weekend
description: Georgia State Road Race Weekend. This year's Georgia State Road Race will offer a whole weekend of racing in historic Calhoun Georgia. A morning time trial will loosen up the legs followed by a fast downtown criterium. The main event is Sundays Road Race in the rolling hills of Gordon County. All races will offer cash payouts and the Sunday Road Race will additionally include State Championship Jerseys for all the race winners.
course:
Our morning Time Trial is an 11.5 mile out and back course through Sugar Valley. The course is rolling to flat, offering a great venue for time trialist and features a downtown finish. 
The afternoon criterium is in downtown Calhoun, convenient to shopping and dinning. 
The road race is entirely in Gordon County. The 26 mile loop is farm county with many low traffic roads, rolling hills, and a few short climbs to shake things up.
registration: Registration is available online at usacycling.org or race day. There is a $15 day of registration fee. Online registration closes at midnight the Thursday before the event.
notes:
Helmets are mandatory at all times
USAC license required*1 day and annual available on site
directions:
Time Trial Start Address: 109 King St N, Calhoun, GA 
Criterium: 106 N Wall St, Calhoun, GA 30701
RR: 7494 Fairmount Hwy SE, Calhoun, GA 30701
